And they just went live in July.

00:23:12.770 --> 00:23:14.950
But they raised $4.2 billion.

00:23:14.950 --> 00:23:19.900
So my estimate, my prediction,
is EOS is going to be real

00:23:19.900 --> 00:23:22.030
and going to be around.

00:23:22.030 --> 00:23:25.360
They've taken $1 billion
of that $4.2 billion

00:23:25.360 --> 00:23:31.370
and set up a Kickstarter
sort of venture firm

00:23:31.370 --> 00:23:35.570
literally so that they could
maybe support some of you.

00:23:35.570 --> 00:23:39.110
You could be knocking on
the EOS venture firm's door

00:23:39.110 --> 00:23:40.610
and saying fund me.

00:23:40.610 --> 00:23:41.750
I've got a great idea.

00:23:41.750 --> 00:23:44.450
And they'd have one
condition, amongst others.

00:23:44.450 --> 00:23:47.570
You'd have to use
EOS as the platform.

00:23:47.570 --> 00:23:51.440
So it's a self-reinforcing
business model.

00:23:51.440 --> 00:23:54.320
NEO is the other big
one that I'd mention,

00:23:54.320 --> 00:23:58.640
which was started two years ago
out of China, a lot of people

00:23:58.640 --> 00:24:01.280
think with the backing of
the Chinese government.

00:24:01.280 --> 00:24:05.000
Even if not officially,
certainly with the verbal

00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:08.900
and help of there.

00:24:08.900 --> 00:24:11.440
Some people think of it
as the Ethereum of China,

00:24:11.440 --> 00:24:14.420
but it does use a
different proof of work.

00:24:14.420 --> 00:24:15.670
And those are the main ones.

00:24:15.670 --> 00:24:17.870
Ethereum Classic is
there because there

00:24:17.870 --> 00:24:25.660
was a hard fork off of Ethereum
after the DAO circumstance.

00:24:25.660 --> 00:24:29.490
Any quick questions
about the platforms?

00:24:29.490 --> 00:24:32.910
And NEO and EOS
are thought to be

00:24:32.910 --> 00:24:36.030
a little bit higher
throughput and faster because

00:24:36.030 --> 00:24:39.720
of the different proof of
work that each of them have.

00:24:39.720 --> 00:24:43.626
So maybe they're more scalable
than Ethereum long term.

