00:25:27.520 --> 00:25:31.962
to single-language
programming platforms?

00:25:31.962 --> 00:25:35.700
Which one do you think
has more potential?

00:25:35.700 --> 00:25:40.690
PROFESSOR: The question is,
do multi-language platforms

00:25:40.690 --> 00:25:44.230
have more potential or less
than single-language platforms?

00:25:44.230 --> 00:25:45.660
I haven't done a real study.

00:25:45.660 --> 00:25:49.190
My gut tells me that
there's some trade-offs.

00:25:49.190 --> 00:25:51.010
So a multi-language
platform probably

00:25:51.010 --> 00:25:53.620
allows for more
development of apps,

00:25:53.620 --> 00:25:56.170
just like on the
internet, if you

00:25:56.170 --> 00:26:00.040
can have more app development.

00:26:00.040 --> 00:26:02.770
Though if you have only
one single language,

00:26:02.770 --> 00:26:06.490
you might have fewer
vulnerabilities,

00:26:06.490 --> 00:26:10.060
vulnerabilities either
to attack or coming down.

00:26:10.060 --> 00:26:14.050
So there's probably
some trade-offs.

00:26:14.050 --> 00:26:19.870
And I'm more into
democratizing capital markets,

00:26:19.870 --> 00:26:22.550
so probably my biases
would be to the ones that

00:26:22.550 --> 00:26:24.560
have multi-language potential.

00:26:24.560 --> 00:26:27.830
But I can't say for sure
whether it will necessarily

00:26:27.830 --> 00:26:32.330
win, because there are some
trade-offs, if that helps.

00:26:32.330 --> 00:26:36.170
So we'll take a view of all of
these later in the semester.

